{[%evp 0,10,22,25,50,-2,-2,-17,-17,-4,20,20,22]} 1. e4 c5 2. c3 {In this
lecture we will cover the Alapin Sicilian. Our aim is to find lines that give
us easier play with a lot of chances to fight for the win.} d5 3. exd5 Qxd5 4.
d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 e6 {There are many other options like Bg4, Nc6, etc. But after
investigating a lot of time in this position I figured out the text move is
quite intresting as well. As it allows us to play for a win without taking many
risks. As we will see in the files, we will develop our light-squared bishop
through b6-Ba6 or Bd7-Bb5. Overall it is a very exciting and underrated
system.} *

