192,129,181,202,205,205,206,184,194,223,361,266,382,378,378,383,424,424,468,
480,480,443,456,504,547,519,523,529,691,529,529,533,578,582] A good online
game showcasing the dangers for Black in the old-main line.} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6
3. c3 d5 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. d4 Nc6 6. Be3 cxd4 7. cxd4 Nf6 {7... Bb4 is our
preference} 8. Nc3 Qd6 9. Bd3 Be7 10. O-O O-O 11. a3 $14 {White has a very
good version of the isolated queen's pawn.} b6 12. Qe2 {There are no Qh5 lines
possible now.} Bb7 13. Rad1 {Correct strategy focusing on the center.} (13.
Rac1 {White should instead place his rooks on e1 & d1 to focus on the center.}
Rac8) 13... Rfe8 14. Rfe1 Rad8 15. Bb1 g6 16. h4 Nd5 17. Ne4 Qb8 18. Ba2 {
Black is constantly under pressure!} Nf6 19. Neg5 Bf8 20. b4 (20. Nxf7 {
was the best according to the computer and it wins quickly.} Kxf7 21. Ng5+ Kg7
22. Nxe6+ Rxe6 23. Bxe6) 20... a5 (20... h6 21. h5 $3 (21. Nh3) 21... Nxh5 22.
Nxf7 Kxf7 23. b5) 21. b5 Ne7 22. Ne5 Ned5 23. Ngxf7 Rc8 24. Qf3 Bg7 25. Nh6+
Bxh6 26. Bxh6 Rc3 27. Rd3 Rxd3 28. Qxd3 Re7 29. Bg5 Rc7 30. Bxf6 Nxf6 31. Bxe6+
Kg7 32. d5 Re7 33. Qd4 Bxd5 34. Nd7 Rxd7 35. Bxd7 Qc7 36. Bc6 Bf7 37. g4 Qc8
38. g5 Qg4+ 39. Qxg4 Nxg4 40. f3 {Black Resigned} 1-0

