{A good game by both side in the parallel hanging pawns line!} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3
(2. c3 {is our move order.} d5 3. exd5 Qxd5 4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 e6 {Transposes.})
2... e6 3. c3 d5 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. d4 Nf6 6. Be3 cxd4 7. cxd4 (7. Qxd4 Nc6) (7.
Nxd4 Be7 8. c4 Qa5+) 7... Bb4+ $1 {This is the best system for Black here} 8.
Nc3 O-O 9. Bd3 b6 $1 10. O-O (10. Qe2 Bb7 11. O-O Qh5) 10... Bxc3 11. bxc3 Ba6
12. Bxa6 {is the best move; to misplace our knight.} (12. Rc1 Bxd3 13. Qxd3
Qxa2 14. c4 Qa4) (12. Re1 Bxd3 13. Qxd3 Rc8 14. Ne5 Nc6 (14... Nbd7 15. Nxd7
Qxd7 16. c4) 15. Nxc6 Qxc6 16. Rec1 Qc4 17. Qxc4 Rxc4) 12... Nxa6 13. Ne5 (13.
Qe2 Nb8 (13... Nc7 {The knight is aimless on c7. It is hardly ever a good move
in this line.} 14. c4 Qb7 15. a4 {We cannot play chess this way.}) 14. c4 Qd6
15. Rfd1 Nc6 {Black would like to exchange pieces and play the endgame.}) (13.
Qd3 {Allows a small trick with ...Nc5} Nc5 14. Qb5 Nce4 {Black is doing great.}
) 13... Nb8 {The only correct retreat.} 14. c4 Qb7 {The game is about equal
now. You can study the rest of the game by your own.} 15. a4 (15. Rc1 Nbd7 16.
Nxd7 Nxd7 (16... Qxd7) (16... Qxd7 17. Re1 Rac8 (17... h6 18. Qf3 Kh7 19. Bxh6
Kxh6 20. Qh3+ Kg6 21. Rc3 Nh5 22. Qg4+ Kh6) (17... Rfc8 18. Bg5 Ne8) (17... Qb7
) 18. Bg5) 17. c5 (17. Qe2 Rac8 18. Rfd1 Qe4 19. f3 Qb7 20. f4 Qe4 21. Qd3 Qxd3
22. Rxd3 b5 (22... Rfd8 23. c5 Nxc5 24. Rdc3) 23. c5 Nf6 24. Rb1) 17... Rac8)
15... Nc6 16. Qf3 Rfc8 17. Rfb1 Qc7 18. Nxc6 Qxc6 19. a5 Qxf3 20. gxf3 bxa5 21.
c5 Nd5 22. Rxa5 a6 23. Rb7 Kf8 24. Kf1 Ke8 25. Ke2 Rc7 26. Rb3 Kd7 27. Kd3 Kc8
28. Rba3 Kb7 29. Ke4 Rc6 30. Ra1 Ka7 31. h4 Rd8 32. R5a3 Rb8 33. Kd3 h5 34. Rg1
g6 35. Rga1 Rb2 36. Ke4 Rb4 37. Bd2 Rb7 38. Be3 Rb2 39. Kd3 Kb7 40. Ke4 Rb4 41.
Bd2 Rb2 42. Be3 Ka7 43. Kd3 Rb7 44. Ke4 Rb2 1/2-1/2

