{A good game by Black highlighting the problems of the Qe2 line in the Bb4
line.} 1. e4 c5 2. c3 d5 3. exd5 Qxd5 4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 e6 6. Be3 cxd4 7. cxd4
Bb4+ 8. Nc3 O-O 9. Bd3 b6 10. Qe2 Bb7 11. O-O Qh5 {Our way of meeting Qe2 line.
} 12. Ne5 Qxe2 13. Bxe2 Nbd7 14. a3 (14. Nxd7 Nxd7 15. a3 Bxc3 16. bxc3 Rac8 {
We will put more pressure in the endgame.}) 14... Bxc3 15. bxc3 Nxe5 16. dxe5
Nd5 17. Bd2 Rac8 $2 {After this move White is better but it doesnt really
matter as it was a blitz game.} (17... Ne7 $1 18. c4 Rfd8 19. Bb4 Nc6 20. Bd6
Nd4 21. Bd3 Nb3 22. Ra2 Ba6 $17) 18. c4 Ne7 19. Bb4 Rfe8 20. Rfd1 Rc7 21. Bd6
Rcc8 22. c5 bxc5 23. Bb5 Bc6 24. Ba6 Rcd8 25. Bxc5 Nd5 26. Bd6 Nc3 27. Rdc1 Bb5
28. Rxc3 Bxa6 29. Rc7 Ra8 30. Bc5 Rec8 31. Rxc8+ Rxc8 32. Bxa7 g5 33. h3 Kg7
34. a4 Kg6 35. Rd1 Bb7 36. a5 Bd5 37. Bd4 Rc6 38. Ra1 Ra6 39. Bb6 Kf5 40. Re1
h5 41. f3 h4 42. Re2 Ra8 43. Kf2 Rc8 44. a6 Bc4 45. a7 Bxe2 46. Kxe2 Rc2+ 47.
Kd3 Ra2 48. Bd4 Kf4 49. Bf2 Kxe5 50. Kc4 Kd6 51. Kb5 Kc7 52. Be3 f6 53. Kc4 Kb7
54. Bd4 e5 55. Bc5 Rxg2 56. Kd5 Rg3 57. Ke6 Rxf3 58. Be7 e4 59. Bxf6 Rxf6+ 60.
Kxf6 e3 0-1

