1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. c3 d5 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. d4 Nf6 6. Be3 cxd4 7. cxd4 (7. Bxd4
{is absuloutely harmless.} Nc6 8. Bxf6 Qxd1+ 9. Kxd1 gxf6 {Black is already
better.}) 7... Bb4+ 8. Nc3 O-O 9. Bd3 b6 10. O-O Bxc3 11. bxc3 Ba6 12. Bxa6
Nxa6 13. Qa4 Nb8 (13... Qb7 {is also possible.}) 14. c4 Qd7 15. Qb3 (15. Qxd7
Nbxd7 16. Rac1 Rac8 {Objectivelty this is equal but Black has easier play.})
15... Nc6 16. Rfd1 {White wants to create a strong passed pawn.} Rac8 (16...
Rfd8 {allows an annoying} 17. Bg5) 17. Qd3 h6 {Protecting against Bg5 threats.}
18. Qe2 Rfd8 19. Rac1 Qb7 20. Ne5 (20. h3 {should be played.}) 20... Nxe5 21.
dxe5 Nd7 22. Bf4 Nc5 {with some strong play in the center, Black is better.}
23. f3 Qa6 24. Be3 Nb7 25. Rxd8+ Rxd8 26. Kf2 Qa5 27. f4 Nc5 28. Bxc5 Rd2 29.
Be3 Rxe2+ 30. Kxe2 Qxa2+ 31. Kf3 a5 32. Bxb6 a4 33. Be3 Kf8 34. c5 Ke8 35. c6
Kd8 36. Rd1+ Kc8 37. Rd6 a3 38. g4 Qb3 39. Ke2 a2 40. Bd4 Qc4+ 41. Kf2 Qxd4+
