{A great model game by Black!} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. c3 d5 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. d4
Nf6 6. Na3 a6 7. Nc2 Nbd7 $5 {also good is Nc6 or the simple 7...cxd4! but i
think 7... Nbd7 is more complicated in order to play for a win !} (7... Nc6 $5
8. Be2 cxd4 9. Ncxd4 Nxd4 10. Qxd4 Qxd4 11. Nxd4 e5 12. Nf3 (12. Nb3 Be6 13.
O-O O-O-O $132) 12... Bd6 13. O-O O-O $132 (13... Be6 $132)) (7... cxd4 $1 8.
Nfxd4 Nc6 $132 (8... Be7 $132)) 8. Be3 (8. Be2 $5 cxd4 $5 (8... Be7) 9. Ncxd4 (
9. Qxd4 b6 10. O-O Bb7 $132) 9... b6 10. O-O (10. Nd2 $6 Bb7 11. Bf3 Qe5+ 12.
Qe2 Qxe2+ 13. Nxe2 O-O-O $3 $15) 10... Bb7 $132 11. Be3 Be7 12. Qc2 Qd6 $3 (
12... O-O 13. Rfd1 (13. Rad1 Qxa2) 13... Rfd8) 13. Rad1 Qc7 14. Rfe1 O-O $132 {
with an at least equal game for black !}) (8. Bd3 b6 9. O-O Bb7 10. Bf4 Qc6 11.
Re1 Bd6 12. Bxd6 Qxd6 $132) 8... b6 $1 9. Bd3 $6 {this bishop should better go
to e2 hoping for Bf3 at some moment !} (9. c4 $6 Qc6 $15 10. Be2 Bb7 11. O-O
Bd6 12. dxc5 bxc5 $1 $17 {x Nf3 , x Nc2 !}) (9. dxc5 Bxc5 10. Qxd5 Nxd5 11.
Bxc5 Nxc5 12. Ncd4 Bb7 $17) (9. Be2 Bb7 10. O-O Be7 $132 (10... Qc6 $5)) 9...
Bb7 10. Qe2 Be7 11. c4 Qh5 $15 12. Nd2 (12. O-O cxd4 (12... O-O $5 $36) (12...
Bxf3 $5 13. Qxf3 Qxf3 14. gxf3 O-O $132 {it is about equal for the moment..but
one mistak by white can be fatal wth this pawn structure!}) 13. Nfxd4 Qxe2 14.
Bxe2 O-O $15 {bad ...horses for white!}) 12... Qxe2+ 13. Bxe2 cxd4 14. Bxd4
O-O-O 15. O-O Bc5 16. Bf3 Ne5 17. Bxb7+ Kxb7 18. Bc3 Nd3 19. Bxf6 gxf6 20. Ne4
Be7 21. b3 f5 22. Ng3 Bc5 23. Ne1 Ne5 24. a3 Rd2 25. b4 Bd4 26. Rb1 Rc8 27. c5
bxc5 28. bxc5+ Ka7 29. Nf3 Nxf3+ 30. gxf3 Rxc5 0-1

