{[%evp 0,32,30,8,43,35,28,13,7,21,15,15,21,27,15,21,15,-7,12,4,10,10,13,7,13,
-5,9,2,2,-24,-9,-21,-16,-13,-20]} 1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 (3. Nf3 $5 d6 $1 {
most likely we must transpose to the line of the open Sicilian that we play!} (
3... e6 $2 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Qc7) (3... e5 4. c3 (4. Nxe5 Qa5+) 4... dxc3 5.
Nxc3 {with practical compensation}) 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6) 3... dxc3 $1 {
of course we take the pawn!} 4. Nxc3 Nc6 5. Nf3 e6 6. Bc4 (6. Bd3 $6 Bb4 ({
or} 6... d6 7. O-O Nf6 {and White doesn't have sufficient compensation})) 6...
Bb4 $1 {A very simple and good system against the Morra. Practically, it puts
an end to this opening. Black not only is a pawn-up, but in most cases, he
also has the better pawn structure. All for just some small possibility of an
attack by White. Generally, the idea is Nc6, e6, Bb4!, Nge7 and Bxc3 and d5! (
before castling!)} (6... d6 {White's idea is to play for activity, for example}
7. O-O Nf6 8. Qe2 Be7 9. Rd1 Qc7 10. Bg5) 7. O-O (7. Bd2 Nge7 8. O-O O-O 9. Re1
(9. a3 Bxc3 10. Bxc3 d5 11. exd5 exd5 (11... Nxd5 $17 12. Bxd5 Qxd5 13. Qxd5
exd5 14. Rfd1 Bg4 $3 (14... Rd8) 15. Rxd5 Bxf3 16. gxf3 Rad8 17. Rad1 Rxd5 18.
Rxd5 Rd8 19. Rxd8+ Nxd8 $17) 12. Bd3 Bf5 (12... Bg4 13. Bxh7+ Kxh7 14. Ng5+ Kg8
15. Qxg4 Qc8 16. Ne6 g6 (16... Ng6 17. Rfe1 d4) 17. Qh4)) 9... d5 $15 {Black
won an instructive blitz game after:} 10. exd5 exd5 11. Bb3 Bg4 12. a3 Ba5 13.
Qe2 Re8 14. Qd3 Bf5 15. Qf1 Qd6 16. h3 Rad8 17. Rad1 h6 18. Nh4 Be6 19. Nf3 a6
20. Bc1 Bxc3 21. bxc3 Ng6 22. Nd4 Nxd4 23. cxd4 Bd7 24. Qd3 Bb5 25. Qf3 Rxe1+
26. Rxe1 Bc6 27. Be3 Re8 28. Bc2 Bd7 29. Rb1 b5 30. Rc1 Rc8 31. Qe2 Qxa3 32.
Qd3 Qxd3 33. Bxd3 Rxc1+ 34. Bxc1 Ne7 35. Ba3 Bf5 36. Bxe7 (36. Bxb5) (36. Bxf5
Nxf5) 36... Bxd3 37. Bb4 g5 (37... h5 38. h4 f5 39. f4 (39. g3 f4) 39... Kf7
40. Kf2 Ke6 41. Ke3 Be4 42. g3 Kd7 43. Kd2 Kc6 44. Ba5 (44. Kc3 Kb6) 44... b4
45. Bxb4 Kb5 46. Kc3 a5 47. Bc5 Ka4 48. Bf8 g6 49. Be7 Kb5) 38. g3 Bf5 39. h4
gxh4 40. gxh4 Kg7 41. f4 Kg6 42. Kf2 Bb1 43. Kg3 h5 (43... f5) 44. Kf3 Kf5 45.
Bd6 (45. Ba5 Bc2 46. Bb4 Bd1+ 47. Ke3 Kg4 48. Be7 (48. Ba5 f5 49. Bd8 b4) 48...
a5) (45. Be1 Bc2 46. Bb4 Bd1+ 47. Ke3 Kg4 48. Be1 Bb3 (48... Bc2 49. Kd2 Bf5
50. Ke3 Be4)) 45... a5 46. Bc7 a4 47. Bd6 Bc2 48. Bb4 Bd1+ 49. Ke3 Kg4 50. Be7
f5 51. Kd2 Bb3 52. Ke3 Bc4 53. Bb4 Kxh4 54. Be7+ Kg4 55. Bd6 h4 56. Kf2 h3 57.
Kg1 Kg3 58. Bb4 h2+ 59. Kh1 Kh3 60. Be1 Bd3 61. Bg3 Be4#) 7... Nge7 {This is
the initial position of the Bb4 system against the Morra.} 8. Bg5 (8. Qe2 Bxc3
9. bxc3 d5 10. exd5 exd5 11. Rd1 O-O 12. Ba3 (12. Bd3 Bf5 (12... Bg4 $2 13.
Bxh7+ Kxh7 14. Ng5+) 13. Bxf5 Nxf5 14. Qd3 g6 (14... Nfe7) 15. Qxd5 Qxd5 16.
Rxd5 Rfd8 17. Rxd8+ Rxd8 18. Bg5 Rd3 19. Rc1 Kg7 $15) (12. Bxd5 Nxd5 13. c4 Nc3
) 12... Re8 $15 (12... Be6)) (8. e5 d5 $1 (8... Ng6 $1 9. Qe2 O-O 10. Rd1 Qc7
11. Nb5 Qb8 12. a3 Be7 $19 13. Re1 a6 14. Nc3 Bd8 (14... d5 15. exd6 Qxd6 $19))
9. exd6 Qxd6 10. Qe2 Bxc3 11. bxc3 O-O 12. Rd1 Qc7 13. Bg5 Nd5 14. Bxd5 exd5
15. Rxd5 Be6 (15... Bg4) 16. Rdd1 Rfe8) (8. Nb5 $1 {SOS!!! THIS IS A LINE I
BETTER REMEMBER BY HEART! BECAUSE I NEED TO GIVE THE PAWN BACK, BUT I HAVE A
CLEAR ADVANTAGE!} d5 $1 9. exd5 exd5 10. Bxd5 Nxd5 11. Qxd5 O-O $1 12. Qxd8 (
12. Qb3 Be6 $15 13. Qc2 h6 14. Bf4 Qf6 $17) 12... Rxd8 13. Nc7 Rb8 14. Bf4 Bg4
15. Ne5 Nxe5 16. Bxe5 Rbc8 $17) (8. Re1 O-O $1 {HERE, i need to castle first
of course} (8... Bxc3 9. bxc3 d5 10. exd5 exd5 11. Bxd5) 9. e5 (9. Bf4 Bxc3 10.
bxc3 d5 11. exd5 exd5 12. Bd3 (12. Bb3 Bg4 13. Qd3 Bf5 (13... Qa5 14. Bd6 (14.
Rad1 Rac8 15. Bxd5 Nxd5 16. Qxd5 Qxd5 17. Rxd5 Bxf3 18. gxf3 Rfd8) 14... Rfe8))
12... Bf5 $17 (12... Bg4 $4 13. Bxh7+) 13. Bxf5 Nxf5 14. Qd3 Nfe7 $1 (14... Qd7
15. Rad1 Rad8 16. c4 d4 17. Ne5 (17. h3 Rfe8 18. Rxe8+ Rxe8 19. g4 Nfe7 20.
Nxd4 Nxd4 21. Qxd4 Qxd4 22. Rxd4 Ng6) 17... Nxe5 18. Rxe5 g6 19. Rd5 Qe6 20.
Rxd8 Rxd8 21. g4 Ne7 22. Qxd4 Re8) 15. Rad1 Re8 $1 $17 (15... h6 $17) (15...
Rc8 $15) 16. h3 a6 (16... h6)) 9... d5 (9... Ng6 $1 $17 10. Bg5 Qa5 $17 (10...
Be7) 11. Bd2 Ncxe5) 10. exd6 Qxd6 11. Qe2 Bxc3 12. bxc3 Nd5) (8. Bf4 $6 Bxc3 9.
bxc3 d5 (9... O-O $6 {we never allow} 10. Bd6) 10. exd5 (10. Bd3 dxe4 11. Bxe4
Qxd1 12. Rfxd1 O-O 13. Rab1 Re8 (13... f6) (13... Nd5 14. Bxd5 exd5 15. Rxd5 b6
(15... Be6) 16. Rd6 Bf5 (16... Na5)) 14. Nd4 Nxd4 15. cxd4 Nd5 16. Bxd5 exd5
17. Rdc1 b6 18. Rc7 Ba6 19. h3 Bc4) 10... exd5 11. Bd3 O-O 12. Qc2 (12. Re1 Bf5
$15) (12. Ne5 Bf5 13. Bxf5 Nxf5 14. Qd3 Nxe5 15. Qxf5 Nc6 16. Rad1 Qc8 (16...
Ne7) 17. Qxc8 Raxc8 18. Rxd5 Rfd8 19. Rfd1 Rxd5 20. Rxd5 Kf8 (20... Rd8) 21.
Rd7 Rd8 22. Rxd8+ Nxd8) (12. Bxh7+ $4 {Rule of thumb: if Black's piece can
cover the h7-b1 diagonal, the sacrifice doesn't work} Kxh7 13. Ng5+ Kg8 14. Qh5
Bf5 $19) (12. Bc2 {this variation is just to show another example when the
Greek gift sacrifice doesn't work} Qa5 13. h3 Qa6 14. Rb1 b6 15. a4 Bb7 16.
Bxh7+ Kxh7 17. Ng5+ Kg8 18. Qh5 Qd3 19. Rbd1 Qg6) 12... Ng6 13. Bg3 Bg4 $15)
8... Bxc3 $1 9. bxc3 d5 (9... f6 10. Be3 d5 (10... O-O 11. Qd6) 11. exd5 exd5
12. Bb3 Be6 13. Bc5 O-O 14. Re1 Bf7 15. Nd4 Re8 16. Nxc6 Nxc6 (16... bxc6) 17.
Rxe8+ Qxe8 18. Bxd5 Bxd5 19. Qxd5+ Qf7 20. Qf3 Rd8) 10. exd5 exd5 11. Bb3 f6
12. Bh4 Be6 $1 13. Re1 Bf7 14. Nd4 Nxd4 15. Qxd4 O-O $15 16. Rad1 {The theory
ends here and Black is better. He can play several logical moves and WE ALWAYS
KEEP IN MIND THAT IF WE HAVE TO, WE RETURN THE EXTRA PAWN, EXCHANGE SOME
PIECES, GET TO A BETTER ENDGAME AND PUSH HARD FOR THE WIN!} Re8 $17 (16... Nc6
17. Qc5 Qa5 (17... Re8 18. Rxe8+ Qxe8 19. Bxd5 Bxd5 20. Qxd5+ Kh8 21. Qd7 Qxd7
22. Rxd7 Rd8 23. Rxd8+ Nxd8 {Even here, Black has chances to push for a win.})
18. Qxa5 Nxa5 19. Bxd5 Rad8 20. Bxf7+ Kxf7 $15) (16... Nf5 17. Qf4 Nxh4 18.
Qxh4 Qc7 $15) *

