{This is how we play with black! Look how the great Boris Gelfand got the
upper hand against me in the 2000 Olympiad in Istanbul!} 1. e4 c5 2. b3 d6 3.
Bb2 Nf6 (3... a6 {is also playable}) 4. Bb5+ Nbd7 $1 (4... Nc6 $2 5. Bxc6+ $1 {
thank you!}) 5. Qe2 g6 $1 6. f4 (6. Bxf6 exf6 7. Nc3 Bg7 $15) 6... Bg7 7. Nf3
O-O 8. O-O (8. d3 $2 Qa5+ 9. Nc3 Nxe4 $17) 8... a6 9. Bxd7 Qxd7 $3 $15 {
The Bc8 will go to b7! ...and this queen may at any moment appear on g4!} 10.
Nc3 (10. d3 b5 $15 (10... Qg4 $3 11. Bxf6 Bxf6 (11... exf6 $15) 12. e5 Bg7 $15)
) 10... b5 11. f5 Bb7 (11... gxf5 12. Nh4 fxe4 13. Nf5) 12. d3 e6 $1 13. fxg6
fxg6 14. Rae1 Rae8 15. a3 Nh5 $15 (15... e5 $1 $15) 16. g3 Qd8 17. Rf2 Nf6 18.
Rff1 Qb6 19. Nd1 e5 20. c4 Bc8 21. Kg2 Bh6 $15 1/2-1/2

