1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Qxd4 Nc6 5. Bb5 Bd7 6. Bxc6 Bxc6 7. Bg5 f6 $3
$15 8. Bh4 e5 9. Qe3 Qa5+ {[%csl Rh4][%cal Gd6d5] We know that 9...h5 is the
best move, but of course Csom didn't have engine access. 9...Qa5+ is actually
also a good move and shows the same idea: we want to play ...d6-d5 after we
break the pin.} (9... d5 10. Nxe5) (9... h5 $3 10. h3 g5 11. Bg3 d5 $17) 10.
Nc3 Ne7 11. O-O O-O-O 12. Rfb1 d5 {Black is already much better and won after
some complications.} 13. b4 Qb6 14. Qe1 dxe4 15. b5 exf3 16. bxc6 Qxc6 17. Nb5
Qc5 18. Qa5 a6 19. Rb3 Nd5 20. Rab1 Rd7 21. gxf3 Be7 22. Bg3 g5 23. Qa4 Rhd8
24. c4 Nb6 25. Na7+ Kb8 26. Nc6+ Qxc6 27. Qxc6 bxc6 28. Rxb6+ Kc7 29. Rb7+ Kd6
