{In the following model games we'll have a look at how to handle White's most
standard plan to transfer the f3-knight to the e3-square on move ten.} 1. e4 c5
2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Qxd4 Nc6 5. Bb5 Bd7 6. Bxc6 Bxc6 7. Nc3 h6 8. O-O e5 9.
Qd3 Nf6 10. Nd2 d5 $1 {not even allowing White to execute the plan, this is
one of the only lines you'll have to know by heart.} *

