1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Qxd4 Nc6 5. Bb5 Bd7 6. Bxc6 Bxc6 7. Nc3 e5 8.
Qd3 h6 9. O-O Nf6 10. Nd2 d5 $1 11. exd5 Nxd5 12. Nxd5 Qxd5 13. Qxd5 Bxd5 14.
Re1 Bd6 15. c4 (15. Ne4 Bc7 {Black keeps the pair of bishops and with it: the
advantage.} (15... Bxe4 {Even this move might offer Black some advantage.} 16.
Rxe4 f5 17. Re2 Kf7 $15)) 15... Bc6 16. c5 Bc7 17. f4 (17. Nc4 f6 18. Nd6+ Kd7
$17 {[%cal Gd7e6]} (18... Bxd6 $17 {also looks really strong.})) 17... O-O (
17... O-O-O {is even better, bring the king to safety and activate the a8-rook
in one move.} 18. fxe5 Ba5 $19) 18. fxe5 Rad8 19. b4 Rfe8 20. Nc4 Rd4 21. Nd6
Bxd6 22. cxd6 Rxd6 {and although Black didn't convert this position, he was
clearly better and got a nice position out of the opening.} 23. Kf2 Rd4 24. a3
Rc4 25. Ra2 {(=)} Be4 26. Bf4 Bb1 27. Rxb1 Rxf4+ 28. Kg3 Re4 29. Rc1 R8xe5 30.
Rc7 Re7 31. Rac2 Re3+ 32. Kf2 Re2+ 33. Kf1 Kh7 34. Rxe7 Rxe7 35. Kf2 Kg6 36.
