plan, but Black doesn't have to play ...e7-e5. Note that if White castles
first, Black is in time to meet the Nf3-d2-plan with ...d6-d5.} (8. O-O e5 9.
Qd3 Nf6 10. Nd2 d5 $1) 8... Nf6 (8... e5 9. Qd3 Nf6 10. Nc4 Be7 11. Ne3 $11 {
White has reached the optimal setup, but this does not mean White is better.
The position is still unclear, but why allow it?}) 9. Nc4 g6 $1 10. Ne3 Bg7 11.
