1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Qxd4 Nc6 5. Bb5 (5. Qe3 g6) 5... Bd7 6. Bxc6
Bxc6 7. Nc3 h6 8. Qd3 {[%cal Gf3d4]} e5 9. Nd5 $6 Nf6 $15 {is the best and the
most simple move.} (9... Bxd5 10. Qxd5 Qd7 $132) (9... Ne7) 10. c4 (10. Nxf6+
Qxf6 {is just easier.} (10... gxf6 $5 {If you take with the pawn you have to
play ...f6-f5 or ...d6-d5 in next couple of moves.} 11. Nh4 (11. c4 f5 $15)
11... d5 $17) 11. O-O $1 {We don't want to castle long because then we would
automatically give White chances for counterplay. After a short castle, we
still have the attack but White has no way to attack us..} Be7 12. Bd2 Qg6 13.
Rfe1 O-O $17 {[%cal Gf7f5]}) 10... Nxd5 11. cxd5 (11. exd5 {is once more a
position that resembles the Nadjorf.} Bd7 12. O-O Be7 (12... g6 {The bishop
would be more active on the g7-square, but it costs more time giving White
time to strike.} 13. c5 $1 $11) 13. c5 O-O $15) 11... Qa5+ $1 12. Bd2 Bb5 $1
$17 {taking away White's right to castle, after this very nice sequence of
moves Black has increased the advantage hugely.} 13. Qe3 Qa6 14. a4 Be7 15. Bb4
Rc8 16. Kd2 Be2 (16... Bd7 $3 17. b3 f5 $19) 17. h4 Rc4 18. Bc3 Bxf3 19. gxf3
Rxa4 20. Rxa4 Qxa4 21. f4 Bf6 22. fxe5 dxe5 23. Rg1 Qa6 24. f4 exf4 25. Qxf4
Bxc3+ 26. bxc3 O-O 27. Qe5 g6 28. h5 Qb6 29. Rg3 Qf2+ 30. Kd1 g5 31. d6 Qf1+
32. Kd2 Qf2+ 33. Kd1 Qf1+ 1/2-1/2

