1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. f3 {White wants to get a Maroczy
bind - but it is not happening!} e5 {Black should try to twist the game into
concrete play.} 6. Nb3 (6. Bb5+ $6 {this is just a mistake here} Nbd7 $3 {
wonderful move.} 7. Nf5 {White thinks that he has everything under control
strategically, but chess is a concrete tactical game as well.} d5 $3 {
Important move to create more counterplay.} 8. exd5 a6 9. Bxd7+ (9. Ba4 $6 b5
10. Bb3 Nc5 $15 {Black will win the d5-pawn back soon.}) 9... Bxd7 $1 10. Qd3 (
10. Ne3 Nh5 $3 $15 {planning Qh4. We somehow managed to create counterplay on
the kingside.}) 10... Nxd5 11. Qxd5 Bxf5 12. Qxe5+ Qe7 13. Qxe7+ Bxe7 14. Nc3 (
14. c3 $4 Bc5 $19 {White should be afraid of death here!}) 14... Bxc2 $15 {
Black has a clear advantage. The double bishop is going to be game-changing.})
6... a5 $5 {a very interesting line with fine attacking chances! Our plan is
to play a4.} 7. Bb5+ (7. c4 $4 {looses on the spot to} Nxe4 $3 $17 {You will
get that in many games.} 8. fxe4 Qh4+ 9. Kd2 a4 10. Qe1 Qd8 $17) (7. a4 {
the problem for White now..is that after a4, the move c4 does not fit well
with his position anymore. And if he ignores ...a5 we simply want to push
further.} Be7 8. Nc3 (8. c4 $6 O-O 9. Be3 Nc6 10. Nc3 Nb4 $5 (10... Be6 11. Nd5
Nd7 $1 12. Be2 (12. Qd2 Nc5 13. Nxc5 dxc5 14. Be2 Nd4 15. Ra3 Bh4+ 16. g3 Be7
17. O-O Bd6 $13) 12... Bg5 $15) 11. Be2 Be6 12. Qd2 Rc8 13. Nd5 Nfxd5 14. exd5
Bf5 15. Rc1 Bh4+ 16. g3 Bf6 $17) 8... O-O 9. Be3 Nc6 10. Qd2 Nb4 11. O-O-O Be6
$132) 7... Bd7 $1 8. Bxd7+ Nbxd7 9. a4 (9. c4 $6 {White has managed to achieve
the maroczy bind but that also means he has ignored lots of other important
things like king safety, development, etc.} a4 10. N3d2 Qb6 $3 {White's pieces
are stuck. This is an awful situation to be in.}) 9... d5 $1 {we intend to
complicate matters, by taking advantage of his f3 move which is weakening his
king!} 10. exd5 Nb6 {planning Nxd5.} 11. O-O (11. Qe2 {is also possible, but
that should not worry us.} Qxd5 12. Nc3 Bb4 13. Bd2 Bxc3 14. Bxc3 O-O {Black
is better with so much space, development and activity.}) 11... Nbxd5 $132 {
Black is in very good shape.} *

