-184,-208,-244,-237,-270,-519,-653] Remark: This nice game of the delayed c3
sicilian, we see Black playing the less accurate 9...Nb8?! ..instead of 9...
Na5!. However, it is worth studyng this game of the super GM Anish Giri to see
some of the typical ideas in these positions!} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. c3 Nf6 4.
Be2 g6 5. O-O Bg7 6. Bb5+ Nc6 7. d4 O-O 8. d5 a6 $1 9. Be2 Nb8 $6 (9... Na5 $1
{is the right move!}) 10. Nbd2 e6 11. c4 $2 {was a very bad move.} (11. dxe6 {
would have been a better choice.} Bxe6 12. Ng5 Bd7 {with equal chances.}) 11...
exd5 12. cxd5 Re8 {White has a very bad version of the benoni.} 13. Bd3 Bg4 14.
a4 Nbd7 15. Re1 Ne5 $17 16. Bf1 Nxf3+ 17. gxf3 Bh5 18. Qb3 Nd7 19. f4 Bd4 20.
Nf3 Bxf3 21. Qxf3 Qh4 22. Be3 Nf6 23. Bxd4 cxd4 24. Rad1 Nxe4 25. Rxd4 Nc5 26.
Rxe8+ Rxe8 27. a5 Qf6 28. Rb4 Re1 29. Kg2 Qf5 30. h3 Qb1 31. Be2 Qc2 32. Bf1
Qc1 33. Be2 Qd2 0-1

