1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. c3 Nf6 4. Be2 g6 (4... Nc6 {is also playable. The play
continues like} 5. d4 cxd4 6. cxd4 Nxe4 7. d5 Qa5+ 8. Nc3 Nxc3 9. bxc3 Nb8 10.
O-O {with equal chances.}) (4... Nbd7 $5 {is another tricky line.}) 5. O-O Bg7
6. Bb5+ (6. Re1 O-O 7. Bf1 Nc6 {with typical play.}) 6... Nbd7 (6... Nc6 {
is the mainline.}) 7. Re1 O-O 8. d4 a6 9. Bd3 $6 {I don't really like this
move, White starts loosing control.} (9. Bf1 $1 {would have been better to
maintain harmony.} e5 10. dxe5 Nxe5 {We should recapture with the knight.})
9... e5 10. d5 b5 $1 11. b3 (11. a4 c4 {typical way to meet a4 ideas.} 12. Bc2
Rb8 {The common follow up planning Nc5 next.} 13. Nbd2 Nc5 14. axb5 axb5 15.
Nf1 Bd7 {Black is better. He will soon take over the a-file and plan f5.})
11... Nb6 $1 12. a4 Bd7 13. a5 {a big mistake! Surprisingly, White is now
strategically lost. The point is White cannot create couterplay on the
queenside. While, Black is so much ready to create his attack on the kingside.
You can study the rest of the game on your own.} Nc8 14. Nbd2 Ne8 $1 (14... Ne7
15. Nf1 Ne8 16. Ng3 f5 17. exf5 gxf5 18. Ng5) (14... Bh6 15. Nf1 Bxc1 16. Qxc1
Ne8 17. Qh6) 15. Nf1 f5 16. exf5 (16. Ng5 f4 17. Ne6 Bxe6 (17... Qe7 18. Nxf8
Qxf8) 18. dxe6 Nc7 19. Be2 h5 20. c4 (20. b4 c4) (20. Nd2 Nxe6) 20... b4 21.
Ra2 Qe7 22. Rd2 Ra7 23. Rd5 Nxe6) (16. Ng3 f4 17. Ne2 g5) (16. Bg5 Bf6 17. Bxf6
Qxf6) (16. Bc2 f4) (16. N3d2 f4 17. f3 g5 18. Be2 Nf6 19. b4 c4 20. Ra2 Ne7 21.
Nb1 (21. Nxc4) 21... Ng6 22. Qc2 h5 23. Bd1 g4 24. Qe2 Rf7 25. Na3 Rc8 26. Rc2
Bh6 27. Kh1 Rg7 28. Nb1 Rc7 29. Nbd2 Bc8 30. Nb1 Kh8 31. Na3 Qg8 32. Nb1 Qh7 (
32... h4) (32... Nh4) 33. Na3 g3 34. h3 Nh4 35. Qd2 Bxh3) 16... gxf5 17. Bg5
Nf6 $17 (17... Bf6 $17) 18. Bc2 h6 19. Bh4 Ne7 20. Ng3 e4 21. Nd2 Ng6 22. Bxf6
Qxf6 23. Re3 Qg5 24. Ngxe4 $3 fxe4 25. Rg3 Qf5 26. Nxe4 Kh8 27. Kh1 Ne5 28.
Nxc5 Qf7 29. Ne4 Qe7 30. Qd2 Bf5 31. Re1 Rae8 32. h3 Qd7 33. Rge3 Bh7 34. Kg1
Rf7 35. Ng3 Ref8 36. R1e2 Bxc2 37. Qxc2 Qd8 38. Nh5 Qg5 39. Nxg7 Qxg7 40. Rg3
Qf6 41. Qd2 Rg7 42. Ree3 Rgf7 43. Re2 Qh4 44. Qd4 Qd8 45. Rg4 Qf6 46. Rg3 Rg7
47. Rxg7 Qxg7 48. Kh1 Qf6 49. Kg1 Rg8 50. Re3 Rg7 51. Rg3 Rxg3 52. fxg3 Qg6 53.
Qh4 Kg7 54. Qe7+ Nf7 55. Kh2 Qc2 56. Qb7 Qf2 57. b4 h5 58. Qxa6 Ng5 59. Kh1 Ne4
60. Qb6 Nxg3+ 61. Kh2 Nf1+ 62. Kh1 Ne3 63. Qc7+ Qf7 64. Qxf7+ Kxf7 65. a6 Nxd5
66. g4 hxg4 67. hxg4 Kf6 68. a7 Nb6 69. Kg2 Na8 70. Kf3 Kg5 71. Kg3 Nb6 72. Kf3 1/2-1/2

