10. a5 $2 {White advances the pawn pretty recklessly. It is not objectively
that bad, but in practical terms it is a mistake.} ({White should have played
in the centre:} 10. Rd1 Bb7 11. e5 (11. Be3 {runs into} Ng4 {, already with
slight problems for White:} 12. Bc1 Qc7 13. h3 Ngf6 14. Be3 Rfd8 $15 15. Bf1
