good for guaranteeing equality, but is not enough for any advantage for White.}
) 10... bxa5 $1 {The question is asked of White how does he intend to
recapture the pawn! If he doesn't manage to do it, Black will happily enjjoy
the material advantage.} 11. Nd2 Nc5 12. Nc4 a4 {Black tries to make it hard
to retake the pawn.} 13. f3 $2 {The beginning of White's downfall.} (13. e5 {
could simplify and possibly hold:} dxe5 14. Qxd8 Rxd8 15. Nxe5 Bb7 16. Nxa4 $11
) 13... d5 $1 {White is ill-prepared for this advance.} 14. exd5 exd5 15. Ne5
Qc7 16. Nb5 Qb6 17. Be3 Ba6 18. Nc3 Bxe2 19. Nxe2 Rfc8 20. Bf2 Qc7 21. Qc3 Bd6
22. Bg3 d4 $1 {Black inititates a well-calculated winning sequence.} 23. Qxd4
Ne6 24. Qc3 Qb6+ 25. Bf2 Qb5 26. Qd3 Qxe5 27. Bg3 Qc5+ 0-1

