Be7 7. c4 O-O 8. d4 cxd4 9. Nxd4 a6 10. Nc3 Qc7 11. Qe2 ({After} 11. Bb3 {
we shall organize our position in the Hedgehog style:} b6 ({After} 11... Nc5 $6
12. Bc2 $1 {our knight is actually doing nothing on c5!}) 12. Be3 Bb7 13. f3
Rac8 14. Rc1 Rfe8 15. Kh1 Qb8 $132 {We have a good version of the typical
Hedgehog, the white light-squared bishop is awkwardly placed on b3 instead of
the f1-a6 diagonal.}) 11... Ne5 12. Bb3 Nc6 (12... Bd7 $1 {This would have been
correct. We want to recapture with the bishop after ...Nc6 Nxc6.} 13. f4 Nc6
14. Nxc6 Bxc6 $132 {With a standard Sicilian position except for the atypical
bishop on b3, which doesn't help White.}) 13. Be3 ({White could have benefited
from} 13. Nxc6 $1 bxc6 (13... Qxc6 $6 {The queenis very misplaced.} 14. Bf4 $16
) 14. Bc2 $14) 13... Na5 14. Rac1 Nxb3 15. Nxb3 b6 16. f3 Bb7 17. a4 Rac8 18.
a5 bxa5 19. c5 dxc5 20. Na4 Nd7 21. Nbxc5 Nxc5 22. Nxc5 Qc6 23. Red1 Rfd8 24.
Rxd8+ Bxd8 25. g3 h6 26. Kg2 Bf6 27. Ra1 Qb6 28. Nxb7 Qxb7 29. Rxa5 Qb3 30. Ra3
Rc2 31. Rxb3 Rxe2+ 32. Kf1 Rxb2 33. Ra3 Rb1+ 34. Ke2 Ra1 35. Rxa1 Bxa1 36. Kd3
Kf8 37. Kc4 Be5 38. Bb6 Bd6 39. Kb3 Ke7 40. Ka4 Kd7 41. Ka5 Kc6 42. Kxa6 h5 43.
Bd4 g5 44. Ka5 g4 45. fxg4 hxg4 46. Bf6 Kc5 47. Ka6 e5 48. Kb7 Kd4 49. Kc6 Bb4
50. Kd7 Kxe4 51. Ke8 Kf5 52. Kxf7 e4 53. Bd4 Bd2 54. Ke7 e3 55. Kd6 e2 56. Bf2
Ke4 0-1

