Nxe5 11. Nxe5 dxe5 12. Be3 Qc7 13. a4 Be6 14. a5 Ng4 15. Bc1 b5 (15... Bh6 $3
$15 {Remember this idea! Black achieves an advantage by trading his passive
dark-squared bishop, e.g.} 16. Bxh6 Nxh6 17. f3 f6 18. Nd2 c4 19. Qe2 Nf7 20.
Kh1 Rfd8 $15) 16. axb6 Qxb6 17. h3 Nf6 18. Qe2 c4 19. Nd2 Rfc8 20. Nf3 Nh5 21.
Ra2 h6 22. Be3 Qb7 23. Kh2 Nf6 24. Qd2 Kh7 25. Ra5 Rd8 26. Qc1 Rab8 27. Ra2 Nd7
28. Rd1 Nf6 29. Rxd8 Rxd8 30. Nd2 Nd7 31. Ra4 Qc6 32. Qa1 Ra8 33. Ra5 Qb7 34.
Ra4 Qc6 35. Bd1 Nc5 36. Ra5 Nb7 37. Ra2 Bf8 38. Be2 Bc5 39. Bxc5 Nxc5 40. Kg1
Rd8 41. Qe1 Qd7 42. Nf3 Nd3 43. Qa1 Qb7 44. Rxa6 Nc1 45. Qxc1 Qxa6 46. Nxe5 Qa2
