{[%evp 0,108,19,38,40,41,66,55,79,9,28,-17,-28,-14,-25,-30,-20,-59,-43,-26,-23,
-17,-28,-22,-16,-57,-32,-56,-30,-32,-23,-23,-29,-29,-29,-17,-18,-28,2,9,10,-27,
3,0,45,-34,-11,-63,-100,-40,-46,-43,-61,-56,-38,-74,-67,-68,-69,-83,-86,-96,
-30,-44,16,-75,-67,-71,-40,-51,-51,-56,-60,-60,-68,-86,-74,-86,-73,-92,-74,-69,
-69,-75,-57,-44,-50,-70,-77,-68,-71,-78,-82,-74,-36,-103,-118,-104,-113,-109,
-126,-124,-116,-149,-141,-164,-124,-192,-164,-29999,-29996]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6
3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. c3 Ngf6 5. Bd3 g6 ({My recommendation is} 5... a6 {with
transpositions, but the game continuation leads to the type of position
relevant for our repertoire.}) 6. Bc2 Bg7 7. d4 O-O 8. a4 (8. O-O {Remember
our main idea in these positions:} e5 9. dxe5 Nxe5) 8... b6 9. O-O Bb7 10. Re1
e6 11. Nbd2 Qc7 12. Bd3 Rac8 13. Nf1 Rfd8 14. Bd2 e5 {After some piece
improvement Black finally decides on the thematic ...e5, which is a good
choice here indeed.} 15. d5 c4 16. Bc2 Nc5 17. Bg5 $6 h6 18. Bh4 $6 {The
bishop is on the path to become misplaced on the kingside.} a6 19. N3d2 b5 20.
axb5 axb5 21. Ne3 Re8 22. Ng4 Nh5 $15 {White is starting to get positionally
outplayed.} 23. Bg3 Nf4 ({The best choice was} 23... Nxg3 $1 24. hxg3 h5 25.
Ne3 Ra8 $17 {But in the game Black also keeps the initiative.}) 24. Qf3 h5 25.
Ne3 Ncd3 26. Reb1 Ra8 27. Rxa8 Rxa8 28. Bxf4 Nxf4 29. g3 Nh3+ 30. Kg2 Ng5 31.
Qe2 Nh7 32. Qd1 Bh6 33. Ra1 Qb6 $2 ({Exchanges on a1 and e3 were the best
choice, leading to a strategically won position:} 33... Rxa1 34. Qxa1 Bxe3 $1
35. fxe3 Bc8 $19 {White has too many weaknesses and passive pieces. Black has
ideas like ...Qd7-h3 and ...Nd7-c5. White resistance will inevitably be broken.
}) 34. Rxa8+ Bxa8 35. Ndf1 Nf6 36. h3 ({Instead of waiting passively, White
should have created his own counterplay:} 36. b3 $1 cxb3 37. Bd3 $15 {, the
position being already very close to full equality.}) 36... Bb7 37. Kh2 Qa7 38.
Qf3 Kg7 39. Qd1 Bc8 $1 $17 {After the long maneuvering phase Black finally
begins the light-square invasion on the kingside.} 40. Kg2 Qd7 $1 41. h4 Qh3+
42. Kg1 Ng4 43. Nxg4 Bxg4 44. f3 Bc8 (44... Be3+ $1 {was an even stronger
possibility, but not an obvious one by any means:} 45. Nxe3 Qxg3+ 46. Ng2 Bxf3
47. Qf1 Bxg2 48. Qxg2 Qe1+ 49. Qf1 Qxh4 $19 {The engine points out that Black
is totally winning. White's bishop is painfully passive and his king has no
shelter against checks.}) 45. b3 cxb3 46. Bxb3 Ba6 47. Qe2 (47. Qa1 $1 {
offered better resistance, pinning the black queen to defence of the bishop
for a time being:} Qc8 48. Kg2 $17) 47... Qc8 $1 {Queen will now invade from
an entirely new direction with decisive effect.} 48. Qd3 Qc5+ 49. Kg2 Qa3 50.
Qc2 Bc8 {Black tightens the net. White finds himself in a kind of a zugzwang.}
51. Qa2 Qc1 52. Qc2 Qe1 53. Nh2 Be3 54. Qe2 Qxe2+ 0-1

