{[%evp 0,18,17,22,52,43,81,31,48,42,55,23,10,-3,-4,-9,-9,-9,-16,-9,-3] In this
section we look at the games resulting from the main line:} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6
3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. O-O a6 5. Bd3 Ngf6 6. c3 e6 7. Re1 Be7 8. Bc2 b5 9. d4 Bb7 {
with examples of both correct (...Qc7, ...Rfc8, ...Bf8-g6-Bg7 and ...e6-e5
ideas in the air) and incorrect (premature ...cxd4, ...d5?) play by Black. We
also look at some games where White took the slow d3 approach and regreted it
later.} *

