{[%evp 0,53,19,38,40,41,66,55,79,50,55,42,32,-9,23,-11,-17,-3,4,-2,-1,3,10,-20,
2,-30,-14,1,7,10,26,23,28,39,47,50,32,10,6,-5,-5,-1,0,43,43,70,70,70,1076,1076,
1076,1118,1135,1173,1164,1182] A nice game by white... although the GM behind
the Black pieces is a great player, he did not perform well in this particular
game... 2 big mistakes for Black, which we must avoid, were: 1) the ...cd4?
move 2) the d6-d5? advance!} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. O-O a6 5. Bd3
Ngf6 6. Re1 e6 ({My recommendation is} 6... g6 {, but the game move is also
playable and leads to the position that can also arise out of our repertoire.})
7. c3 b5 8. Bc2 Bb7 9. d4 cxd4 $2 {A very premature trade.} (9... Be7 {is
correct.}) 10. cxd4 Be7 11. Nbd2 O-O 12. Nf1 Nb6 13. Ng3 (13. b3) 13... Rc8 14.
Bd3 Re8 15. Qe2 Nfd7 ({If Black really wanted ...d5, he should have done it
now:} 15... d5 16. e5 Ne4 17. Nxe4 dxe4 18. Bxe4 Bxe4 19. Qxe4 Nd5 20. Bd2 $14
{with positional compensation for Black.}) 16. b3 d5 $4 {White is much better
anyway, but this is a suicidal choice.} 17. e5 $18 {Now White has a winning
position because he has a strong attack and Black's pieces are very passive on
the queenside!} Nb8 $6 (17... Bb4 18. Bxh7+ $1 $18 {completely crushes Black.})
({With} 17... Nf8 {Black could have at least played on for some time. But
White does not even have to hurry, as Black is completely passive.} 18. Bd2 (
18. h3 Nbd7)) 18. Nh5 Nc6 (18... g6 19. Qe3 $1 $18 {The attack should decide,
e.g.} Nc6 20. Qh6 Bf8 21. Qf4 $18) 19. Nxg7 $3 {A very deep sacrifice. The old
engines needed some time to see White is winning here!} Kxg7 20. Qe3 Rh8 21.
Qh6+ Kg8 22. Ng5 Bxg5 23. Bxg5 Ne7 (23... Qf8 24. Qh5 $1 {White understood
that there's no need to see an immediate forcing win, as White's compensation,
apart from being based on the attack, is also very much positional.} Ne7 25.
Bh6 $1 Qd8 (25... Qe8 26. Qg5+ Ng6 27. Qf6 $18) 26. Re3 Ng6 27. Rg3 Qe8 28. h4
$18 {Black will not hold on for long.}) 24. Bxe7 {Here Black resigned, but...
I continue for a while} Qxe7 25. Re3 f5 26. exf6 ({Alternatively, the prosaic}
26. Rg3+ Kf7 27. Rg7+ $18) 26... Qf8 27. Rg3+ Kf7 28. Bg6+ Kxf6 29. Qg5+ Kg7
30. Bh5# 1-0

